Bauchi – No fewer than 20 persons have been burnt beyond recognition on Sunday in a fatal auto-crash that occured at Mangorori in Tirwun village, which is 3km away from Bauchi metropolis. Daily Independent learnt that the accident involved a Hummer Bus belonging to Borno Express, which was heading to Maiduguri from Jos with 18 passengers and a VW Golf vehicle coming from Misau which was heading to Bauchi with 4 passengers. According to an eyewitness account, the accident was caused as a result of a head-on collision, which made the two vehicles burst into flames. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The eyewitness said that the two vehicles bursted into flames immediately they collided with 20 of the passengers been burnt beyond recognition after a combined team of firefighters from Bauchi put off the fire, in the end, two female passengers survived with degrees of injuries. Confirming the incidence, the Bauchi State Police Command through its PPRO, DSP Ahmed Wakili, said that the charred bodies of the victims have been deposited at the mortuary of Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University Teaching Hospital (ATBUTH) while the two female survivors are receiving treatment at the same hospital. Banks To Rationalise Staff, Branches As Costs Mount I’m In 2023 Presidential Race To Liberate Nigeria — Yahaya Bello Ahmed Wakili though could not confirm the cause of the accident, he said that Police personnel promptly responded to the distress call and joined in the evacuation of the victims.